      </userestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_4fbf0db57b34527c586200c0548d636c">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Yale Gay and Lesbian Alumni Records (RU 956). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <processinfo id="aspace_e6e2086e404f46ced0da186b6c9fcc81">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>Yale University records are arranged and described at the accession level by the creating office. The University Archives creates collection level descriptive records, but typically does no further arrangement and description at the accession level.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <bioghist id="aspace_702b02760d0d44359b31a28ef8a593eb">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The Yale Gay and Lesbian Alumni (GALA) was established in 1983. It sponsors social and educational events, supports the goals and activities of campus gay and lesbian organizations, and promotes an atmosphere of understanding and cooperation among its members and the entire Yale community.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_efb6754b07ece814266acefed8f34a84">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of correspondence, minutes, drafts of constitution and bylaws, newsletters, and news clippings  documenting the activities of the Yale Gay and Lesbian Alumni (GALA).</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_6bd926b6e7dab018f233ac54a78a3279">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged by accession.</p>  
      </arrangement>
